<br>
Methodology:<br>
<br>
I have Suspend 2 so I summon pet - 64 belt, fire weapons, mask of Mardu, Burnout V, flameshield of ro and velocity. Fight to the cortyard with no mobs under the walk through <br>
<br>
I then Suspend pet<br>
<br>
Get up to the walkway - bring pet back - kill the 2 wanderers making sure you dont get too close to either of the buildings.<br>
<br>
Kill the 2 mobs around Neh's house pulling them single with Malosini. There is also one mob in the house with the Black Reaver that makes an uncommon appearance at the door- kill that also. Once these 3 mobs are dead - levi yourself and run around the outside of the house. This will agro the Black reaver - pull it back on the platform and kill it. Remember spam back off on your guarding pet on walkway.<br>
<br>
Black Reavers are dead easy with 65 Earth Pet. The only issue is do not let your pet get out of melee with them. Your pet is a Mob as far as spell mechanics go. Black reavers blind.<br>
While your pet is in melee range of te reaver with its proc &quot;Blinding Fear&quot; the pet will continue wailing on it - but if the pet gets out of melee range it will run away as if feared. This is the way all Blind spells work on Mobs - just ask a pally.<br>
<br>
Ayways if you get arround this little issue Black reavers = cake and they dont seem to enrage.<br>
<br>
Once the reaver is dead Neh will spawn. Med up - its a good idea to have your best heal spell or 2 up for pet boy. When your ready to go rebuff Jobober and sick pet. Mala for good measure but I doubt you will get a chance to land a nuke on it - most of mine are resisted and I dont think I got 1 of my 10 sini's to land.<br>
<br>
I suggest knocking her off the platform - this is because she ends up in the cortyard with no mobs - down there you can push her arround to your hearts content - no problem. Up on the platform you have to be careful of such things as pushing her off with your Host of the Elements if you have it :P not to mention repops if your moving slowly.<br>
<br>
Spells that she liked to cast = <br>
*Invoke Fear (on me a lot) so buff up that MR as much as you can - its frightening running towards that other house full of nasty mobs.<br>
*Complete heal - yes she complete heals once per fight - so just plan to kill her twice. <br>
*Dispell (on me - annul) she seemed to think me having Kei on was cheating so she dispelled me on the first one I did - somewhat annoying - combat this with what junks you get and make sure kei is in slot 5 6 or 7 :P<br>
*Dazzle (on me) the second Neh I killed seemed to also have the ability to cast dazle (none landed) I had 120MR for the battle and the 4 times she cast it it did not stick<br>
<br>
That said she really wasnt difficult - she doesnt enrage so dont freak out when she gets to low health.<br>
<br>
But its nice to know that yet another parts of our Epic is actually Soloable - not to mention - being able to do Black reavers solo is kind of cool for your ranger friends<br>
<br>
